<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.74.10380.figure1>
    dc:description "Figure 1. SEMs of megaspores (a, b, c) and microspores (d, e, f) of Isoetes mississippiensis displaying distal (a, d), equatorial (b, e), and proximal (c, f) views. Megaspores from Schafran MS- 08, microspores from Taylor 6798. Megaspore magnification 200 x; microspore magnification 2000 x." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/109971" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.74.10380.figure2>
    dc:description "Figure 2. SEM detail of megaspore micro-ornamentation. Magnification 2000 x." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/109972" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.74.10380.figure3>
    dc:description "Figure 3. Light microscope image of megaspores of Isoetes mississippiensis from Schafran MS- 07 (left) and MS- 08 (right). Magnification 63 x. Scale bar = 0.3 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/109973" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.74.10380.figure4>
    dc:description "Figure 4. Map showing two localities of Isoetes mississippiensis. Inset: Map of Mississippi with detail area highlighted. Map created using ArcGIS software (Esri)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/109974" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

